Filesystem & Paths

PathResolver (centralizes safe path handling)

    Purpose: canonicalize paths, prevent traversal, enforce root prefix, control symlinks.

    Fields: 
			std::string root_; 
			bool follow_symlinks_;

    Methods:

        std::string join(const std::string& base, const std::string& rel) const

        std::string canonical(const std::string& p) const

        bool isUnderRoot(const std::string& abs) const

        bool exists/isFile/isDir(const std::string&) const

    Notes: used by StaticFileHandler, UploadHandler, CGI script resolution.

FileUtil (small, stateless helpers)

    Methods: 
		bool readAll(const std::string&, std::string& out), 
		size_t sizeOf(const std::string&), bool writeAll(...), 
		bool unlinkSafe(...).

    Notes: wrap errno; no throws.

ErrorPageRegistry (you already have)

    Add: 
		bool loadDirectory(const std::string& dir) to load 4xx/5xx templates.

ETagGenerator (optional but nice)

    Methods: 
		std::string fromStat(time_t mtime, size_t size).

    Use: set ETag header for static files.

HTTP formatting & parsing helpers

MimeTypes (you’ll add this)

    Fields: 
			std::map<std::string,std::string> table_;

    Methods: 
			bool loadFromFile(path), 
			void add(ext, type), 
			const std::string& get(ext) const.

HttpDate (RFC 9110 date formatting)

    Methods: 
			std::string now() (GMT), 
			std::string format(time_t).

    Use: set Date header consistently.

HeaderCase (normalize header keys)

    Methods: 
			static std::string toLower(const std::string&), 
			static bool iequal(a,b).

    Use: store headers case-insensitive; output original casing if you keep it.

UrlCodec

    Methods: 
			std::string percentDecode(const std::string&),
			std::string percentEncode(const std::string&).

    Use: request target, query params, CGI PATH_INFO.

QueryString

    Methods: 
			std::map<std::string,std::string> parse(const std::string&).

    Use: GET params and application/x-www-form-urlencoded.

RangeUtil (optional, if you implement 206)

    Methods: 
			bool parseRange(const std::string& hdr, size_t len, std::pair<size_t,size_t>& out).

Buffering & performance

Buffer (simple growable buffer with watermarks)

    Fields: 
		std::string data_; 
		size_t hi_, lo_;

    Methods: 
		append(const char*, size_t), 
		consume(size_t), 
		size(), 
		highWatermark(), 
		lowWatermark().

    Use: back-pressure in Connection (pause reads when size()>hi_).

BufferPool (optional)

    Methods: 
		std::vector<char*> acquire(size_t), 
		release(char*).

    Use: reduce allocations in hot path (bonus).

OS & processes (thin wrappers)

UniqueFd (RAII for file descriptors)

    Fields: int fd_;

    Methods: 
		get(), 
		release(), 
		reset(int), 
		dtor closes.

    Use: everywhere (sockets, pipes).

Pipe

    Fields: UniqueFd r_, w_;

    Methods: 
		bool open(), 
		int rfd(), 
		int wfd(), 
		closeBoth().

Subprocess (non-CGI specific, but used by CGI)

    Fields: 
		pid_t pid_; 
		Pipe in_, out_, err_;

    Methods: 
		bool spawn(char* const argv[], char* const envp[]), 
		bool killTermKill(), 
		int waitNonBlock(int& status).

Time (monotonic + wall clock)

    Methods: 
		uint64_t nowMs(), 
		uint64_t monotonicMs()

    Use: deadlines for header/body read, write flush, idle keep-alive.

Cross-cutting concerns

Logger (you have it)

    Add levels, request-id support: void withRequest(const std::string& id).info(...) or pass id in calls.

RequestId

    Methods: std::string generate() (e.g., timestamp + counter or 8-byte hex).

    Use: include in access/error logs.

ErrorMapper

    Methods: int fromErrno(int e) → HTTP status, const char* errnoText(int e).

    Use: centralize syscall→HTTP decisions.

Limiter (optional rate limiter)

    Fields: per-IP token bucket map.

    Methods: bool allow(ip).

StringUtil (keep tiny helpers here instead of sprinkling)

    Methods: trim, split, toLower, startsWith, endsWith, asciiOnly (for header tokens)